Task2
	Subtask1 :
		0. Install aws cli
		1. Install ansible on bastion machine
			> sudo apt update
			> sudo apt install ansible
			> create ansible.cfg file at location /etc/ansible/ansible.cfg
				[defaults]
				inventory = /Users/dipeshgarg/learning/demo/4-dynamic-inventory
				host_key_checking = False
				ansible_ssh_user = ubuntu
				remote_user = ubuntu
				private_key_file=/Users/dipeshgarg/files/upgrad-dev.pem
			> vim upgrad_dev.pem file and paste content
			> sudo apt-get update
			> sudo apt-get -y install python3-boto3
		2. Write Inventory file and add details [ip + pem file] for jenkins + app
		3. Write playbook file to install docker on jenkins + app
		https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-use-ansible-to-install-and-set-up-docker-on-ubuntu-20-04
		
	Subtask2 : 
		Demo Purpose installing 
			1. docker on public bastion machine
			2. install jenkins on docker
				docker container run -itd -p 8080:8080 --env JENKINS_OPTS="--prefix=/jenkins" -v jenkins:/var/jenkins_home --name jenkins-local jenkins/jenkins:lts
			3. create ALB with dummy target group with port 80
			4. Create target group for jenkins with port 8080
			5. In listeners insert rule for jenkins and forward all requests to jenkins target group
			6. Fetch the load balancer dns name and apply dns-name/jenkins and you will see the jenkins page
	Subtask3:
		1. Install jenkins manually on jenkins ec2 machine
			docker container run -itd -p 8080:8080 --env JENKINS_OPTS="--prefix=/jenkins" -v jenkins:/var/jenkins_home --name jenkins-local jenkins/jenkins:lts
